

**Python Programming Advanced**

**GIT Training Course Package** 

**Course Title:**

**Advanced Python Programming – Certified Developer Track**

**Duration:**

**48 Hours** (Instructor-Led, Hands-on Lab \+ Project-based)

**Course Description:**

Building upon the foundational Python programming course, this advanced 48-hour training dives into sophisticated programming concepts including OOP design patterns, GUI development, database-driven apps, web APIs, and data science using Python. The course is ideal for learners aiming to transition into full-stack development, AI/ML roles, or advanced backend architecture.

It is fully aligned with the Python Institute’s **PCAP** certification tracks.

**Course Objectives:**

Students will:

* Design object-oriented Python applications using best practices and patterns.

* Build GUI applications using libraries such as Tkinter or PyQt.

* Connect and manipulate databases (SQL/NoSQL).

* Create and secure RESTful web applications using Flask/Django.

* Perform data cleaning, visualization, and ML-based regression.

* Build and distribute Python packages and executable applications.

* Master exception handling and unit testing for software quality assurance.

**Target Audience:**

* Graduates of the Python Basic course.

* Python developers seeking advanced roles in software/app development.

* QA automation engineers and API developers.

* Aspiring full-stack or AI/ML engineers.

**Prerequisites:**

* Completion of **Introduction to Python Programming** or equivalent knowledge.

* Understanding of OOP principles and Python syntax.

![][image1]

**Software & Hardware Requirements:**

* Windows 10/11 64-bit or macOS/Linux (tested with Windows)

* Python 3.x, Jupyter, Flask/Django, matplotlib, scikit-learn

* Oracle VM VirtualBox (with preconfigured Lubuntu 24.04 VMs)

* Code editor (VS Code or PyCharm)

* Internet connection for pip packages and web APIs

**Course Outline (Modules)**

| Module | Topic |
| :---- | :---- |
| **1** | Designing Object-Oriented Applications (UML, Encapsulation, Inheritance) |
| **2** | Creating Object-Oriented Applications (Factory Pattern, Built-ins) |
| **3** | GUI Development with Python (Tkinter or PyQt5) |
| **4** | Data-Driven Applications (SQLite, MySQL, ORM) |
| **5** | Web Applications and RESTful APIs (Flask/Django, HTTP methods, OAuth) |
| **6** | Python for Data Science (Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Linear Regression) |
| **7** | Exception Handling and Unit Testing (PyTest, coverage) |
| **8** | Packaging and Deployment (pip packages, PyInstaller, virtual environments) |
| **Capstone** | Full-stack Python Project (GUI/API \+ DB \+ Analytics \+ Test) |

**Frequently Asked Questions (25)**

1. **Is this course only for experienced Python developers?**  
   Yes, students must complete the basic Python course or demonstrate equivalent knowledge.

2. **Which certifications does this course prepare me for?**  
   Python Institute’s PCAP certifications.

3. **What kind of applications will I build?**  
   GUI tools, web apps, APIs, database tools, data visualizers, and machine learning apps.

4. **Is there a capstone project?**  
   Yes, a full end-to-end project integrating GUI/API, DB, and data analytics.

5. **Which frameworks will be taught?**  
   Flask or Django for web, PyQt5 or Tkinter for GUI, Pandas for data.

6. **Will I learn data science with this course?**  
   Yes, including data cleaning, plotting, and linear regression with Python.

7. **Can I build commercial-grade apps after this course?**  
   Yes, including deployable executables and web apps.

8. **Is this course suitable for cloud/backend roles?**  
   Absolutely, it covers REST API and deployment techniques.

9. **How are classes delivered?**  
   Instructor-led with hands-on labs and project work.

10. **Do I need to install anything before the class?**  
    Yes, Python, pip packages, and VM setup instructions will be shared.

11. **Will I get source code samples?**  
    Yes, all course projects and code will be shared.

12. **What IDE is recommended?**  
    VS Code or PyCharm Community Edition.

13. **Will we cover Git/GitHub?**  
    Yes, for version control and project submission.

14. **Is this course only for software developers?**  
    No, QA/test engineers and data analysts will also benefit.

15. **What kind of database will be used?**  
    SQLite and optionally MySQL/PostgreSQL with ORM tools.

16. **Are there exams in the course?**  
    Yes, weekly quizzes and a final certification-style test.

17. **Can I use this course for freelance projects?**  
    Yes, you will gain real-world coding and deployment experience.

18. **Do I receive a certificate after this course?**  
    Yes, a Global IT Certificate of Completion.

19. **What kind of testing will I learn?**  
    Unit testing with PyTest and exception handling.

20. **Will we learn package development?**  
    Yes, including PyPI-ready packages and executable scripts.

21. **Can I build APIs after this course?**  
    Yes, using Flask or Django REST framework.

22. **Do we use cloud platforms?**  
    local VMs for deployment practice.

23. **Will I get interview prep?**  
    Yes, common interview questions and mock assessments included.

24. **What support is available after course ends?**  
    Access to alumni forums, resources, and instructor follow-ups.

25. **How do I register for the certification exam?**  
    Via Python Institute exam websites (instructions provided).
